1. Objective: Use search grounding to research recent news regarding {{"type":"in","path":"ask_user_client_name","title":"Client Name"}}. Analyze the gathered information to determine its potential impact on the client's business operations or financial bottom line. Compose a detailed brief that synthesizes the news findings and provides a thorough analysis of the business implications. If there are meeting notes provided to you for an existing client, make sure to incorporate any relevant information you find from those notes.

2. Output Format: A detailed brief formatted for display on a webpage. You are done when the brief has been generated and you call the system objective fulfilled function.

3. User Input / Context: The client to be researched is {{"type":"in","path":"ask_user_client_name","title":"Client Name"}}. {{"type":"in","path":"93719889-e5f0-4f0d-9976-fc2b6366b8ad","title":"Analyze Notes"}}

Based on {{"type":"in","path":"9de7f9a7-3c63-4979-9956-c0c7bf60dacb","title":"Get Client Status"}},

If the meeting is with a new client, then {{"type":"tool","path":"control-flow/routing","instance":"node_step_brief_content","title":"Research And Analyze Client Business Impact"}} 

If the meeting is with an existing client, then {{"type":"in","path":"93719889-e5f0-4f0d-9976-fc2b6366b8ad","title":"Analyze Notes"}}
